iv class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-85ec779\" data-id=\"85ec779\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a0d39ac elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"a0d39ac\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Removal: How to remove centipedes from your home<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-48de32d elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"48de32d\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Centipedes are one of the most fearful creatures that can invade any household. They are fast, agile, and have a nasty bite. If you find centipedes in your home, there is no need to panic since there are several effective ways to remove them. Identifying their hiding spots is the first step in removing centipedes from your home. Centipedes love damp and dark environments such as basements, bathrooms and closets.<\/p><ul><li>One way to remove centipedes effectively is by eliminating their food source. Centipedes feed on other insects, such as spiders and cockroaches, so if you eliminate these pests from your house, you will automatically reduce the number of centipedes around your home.<\/li><li>Another effective method for removing centipedes is using sticky traps or glue boards, which can be placed along walls or under furniture where they typically travel.<\/li><li>Lastly, sealing all entry points into your home, like cracks or gaps around doors and windows, is an excellent way to prevent further infestation of this creepy crawlies.<\/li><li>A vacuum cleaner with a hose attachment can be used to suck up the visible ones you see when they come out at night when it&#8217;s cooler outside.<\/li><\/ul><p>By following these methods carefully and consistently, homeowners can get rid of these pesky critters for good!<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Centipedes Identification Color Size Description Color Some centipede species are brightly coloured, while others have dull hues of brown or grey. Size The smallest centipedes measure less than an inch, while the largest can grow up to a 1\/2-foot long. Description Centipedes are characterized by their elongated bodies, divided into numerous segments. The number of &#8230; <a title=\"Centipedes\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/centipedes\/\" aria-label=\"More on Centipedes\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":6747,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"rank_math_lock_modified_date":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[6,37],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-6389","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-pest-control","category-pest-libraries"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/6389"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=6389"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/6389